# WiFi Configuration for start-hotspot.sh
# Copy this file to /mnt/data/wifi.conf and uncomment/modify as needed
#
# AUTOMATIC FALLBACK: If both WiFi and Hotspot are configured, the script will
# try WiFi first and automatically fall back to Hotspot if WiFi connection fails.

# ============================================================================
# WIFI CLIENT MODE (connect to an existing WiFi network)
# ============================================================================
# Required: SSID and PASSWORD

#SSID="YourHomeNetwork"
#PASSWORD="your-wifi-password"

# Optional: Static IP configuration (DHCP will be used if not all present)
#IPADDR="192.168.1.100"
#GATEWAY="192.168.1.1"
#DNS="8.8.8.8"
#IPPREFIX="24"

# ============================================================================
# HOTSPOT MODE (create a WiFi access point)
# ============================================================================
# Required: HOTSPOT_SSID
# Optional: HOTSPOT_PASSWORD (if omitted, creates an open/unsecured network)

#HOTSPOT_SSID="RaspberryPi-Hotspot"
#HOTSPOT_PASSWORD="myhotspotpass"

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
# - Fallback: Configure both sections above for automatic WiFi â†’ Hotspot fallback
# - Interface: wlan0 by default (override with IFACE environment variable)
# - Hotspot IP: NetworkManager assigns 10.42.0.1/24 automatically
# - Open Hotspot: Set HOTSPOT_SSID without HOTSPOT_PASSWORD for unsecured network
